Basic Alarm Clock ⏰

A beginner Python alarm clock project created while learning how to work with date and time in Python using the datetime and time modules.

This program continuously checks the current system time and triggers an alarm message when the user-specified alarm time matches the current time.

Features
User-defined alarm time
24-hour time format support
Real-time clock monitoring
Continuous time checking using loops
Alarm notification when the target time is reached
Automatic program termination after the alarm rings
Uses built-in Python modules only
Concepts Used
Variables
while loops
Conditional statements (if)
User input handling
String formatting using strftime()
datetime module
time module
Infinite loops
Program flow control using break
Real-time data updates
How to Run
Install Python
Download or clone this repository
Run the file using:
python "Basic Alarm Clock.py"
Enter the alarm time in 24-hour format:
10:30:00
The program will continuously display the current time and trigger the alarm when the specified time is reached.
